    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There is a problem with Zend_Queue_Stomp_Client_Connection. When using the Activemq with stom in php.
The CPU load runs sky high when firing multiple parallel requests to it. The load runs so high the machine
becomes unusable.</p>

<p>When you disable the function stream_set_blocking
line 79: //         stream_set_blocking($this-&gt;_socket, 0); // non blocking</p>

<p>The CPU usage is low and the machine stays usable.</p>

